; I# 6 : Bow (short)
INUMBER 6
NAME 32
BOW_WEAPON
WEIGHT 1
VOLUME 6
PARAMETER1 9
PARAMETER2 1804
SUBSTANCE WOOD
CRAFTABLE
ENCRUSTABLE
WORN_AROUND
;
; I# 8 : Bow (composite)
INUMBER 8
NAME 32
BOW_WEAPON
WEIGHT 2
VOLUME 6
PARAMETER1 14
PARAMETER2 1804
SUBSTANCE WOOD
WORN_AROUND
IFPREVERB LOOK -1
  IFVAR INTNUM3 = 1
    ECHO PLAYER ----%cItembit6 = 1 makes this a forester's bow (ex-284)
    ECHO PLAYER Itembit7 = 1 makes this a special bow (ex-1617)
    ECHO PLAYER Itembit8 = 1 makes this a composite bow (ex-1971)%c----
  ENDIF
  IFVAR ITEMBIT6 = 1
    ECHO PLAYER This beautiful bow is made of black yew. The sacred silver oak is etched into the bow.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR ITEMBIT8 = 1
    ECHO PLAYER The bow itself is made of a pure glass-like substance through which can
    ECHO PLAYER be seen a crimson-hued liquid that seems to run in streams throughout the
    ECHO PLAYER bow. Within the streams you can catch faint glimpses of other objects, a
    ECHO PLAYER feather, an eye, a talon and other items that move past too quickly to
    ECHO PLAYER make out.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVAR ITEMBIT6 = 1
  IFPREVERB WIELD -1
    IFVAR ORG ! 15
      DAMAGE ELECTRIC 170 The yew bow twists and turns in your hands, a silvery fire rises out of the earth and the bow bursts into flames.
      ECHO OTHERS As %N starts to wield %a, a silvery fire raises from the earth and the bow bursts into flame and is consumed.
      GMMSG **%n was just tried to wield a Forester's yew bow.
      REMOVEITEM -1
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
  IFPREVERB TAKE -1
    IFVAR ORG ! 15
      CLEARVERB
      DAMAGEPLR ELECTRIC 170 The bow shimmers in a silvery fire, zapping you.
      ECHO OTHERS %N reaches for %a, but it flares with a silvery fire.
      GMMSG **%n just tried to take a Forester bow.
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
  IFPREVERB STEAL -1
    IFVAR ORG ! 15
      CLEARVERB
      DAMAGEPLR ELECTRIC 170 The bow shimmers in a silvery fire, zapping you.
      ECHO OTHERS %N reaches for %a, but it flares with a silvery fire.
      GMMSG **%n just tried to steal a Forester bow.
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVAR ITEMBIT7 = 1
  IFVERB CONCENTRATE -1
    IFVAR ITEMVAL5 ! TIM
      ECHO PLAYER May your aim be true.
      SPELL 512 10
      ECHO Player Let your enemies not harm you.
      SPELL 133 10
      EQUAL ITEMVAL5 TIM
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
  IFVERB LISTEN -1
    ECHO PLAYER For you and only for you I shall reveal the full extent of my powers. If you have need of protection and steady hands you have only to concentrate on me. Should you need your health restored player polish me to a high luster. If you ever need light to see my attention by tapping me.
  ENDIF
  IFVERB WEAR -1
    ECHO PLAYER You sling the bow over your shoulder.
  ENDIF
  IFPREVERB GIVE -1
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER I am for you and no other. I shall be touched by no other hand.
    ECHO OTHERS %n gets a glazed look for a moment and then nods his head absently.
  ENDIF
  IFPREVERB DROP -1
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER I shall not leave your hand we are as one now.
    ECHO OTHERS %n looks like he is about to set the bow down and then changes his mind.
  ENDIF
  IFPREVERB PUT -1
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER No, I will not be seperated from you.
    ECHO OTHERS %n grasps the bow tightly.
  ENDIF
  IFITEM -1 WIELDED
    IFVERB LOAD -1
      ECHO PLAYER As the bow is loaded the arrow shimmers magically.
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
  IFVERB RUB -1
    ECHO PLAYER As you polish the bow lovingly, it glows a soft blue and speaks to you:
    ECHO PLAYER Let my power heal thy wounds.
    ECHO OTHERS %n polishes %a to a high luster and a soft blue glow surrounds %i.
    EQUAL ROUNDTIME 21
    SPELL 318
  ENDIF
  IFVERB TAP -1
    ECHO ALL The bow flares with a brilliant blue light.
    SPELL 113 20
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVAR ITEMBIT8 = 1
  IFVERB CONCENTRATE -1
    ECHO PLAYER A wispy red smoke seems to flow across your mind blotting out all awareness of your surroundings...from far away you can hear chanting...as the smoke grows thicker the chanting seems to grow louder..until you feel yourself floating away, your mind carried on the smoke and chanting...
    ECHO PLAYER Your mind speeds through the smoke like an arrow until you find yourself looking down upon a wooded clearing...you sense the brilliant stars above you and the moon shining brightly upon the clearing...within the clearing are four figures...their bodies smeared with paint. The figures dance rythmically around a blazing fire...their voices raised in a loud chanting...
    ECHO PLAYER One of the figures opens a bag near the fire and lifts a giant, writhing snake from it...holding the snake above his head he dances slowly around the fire, chanting, "Eater of the world accept this reptile into your hungry mouth!", then, still clutching the snake, he thrusts his hands into the fire. The man does not flinch even though you can smell the burning flesh..
    ECHO PLAYER The chanting reaches a fevered pitch as the figure slowly removes his hands from the fire..they now grip a large tube of glass in the shape of a long bow, rather than the snake...the figure rises and joins the others in their dancing...almost immediately another figure detaches himself from the circle and approaches the bag...
    ECHO PLAYER The figure removes a leather flask from the bag and slowly twists the cap off...holding the flask above his head the figure approaches the man holding the glass tube...as the glass tube is tilted towards him the flask bearer intones, "Mother of nature, we give this weapon the strength of bear, so that it may never break!", then pours a reddish liquid from the flask into a hollow end of the glass tube...
    ECHO PLAYER After finishing with the flask the bearer gestures towards another one of the dancing figures who approaches the bag and pulls a screaming eagle from the bag, raising the eagle towards the moon the man quickly tears an eye from his struggling captive and then approaches the bow wielder...intoning, "Mother of nature, grant this weapon the eye of the eagle, so that it may never miss its mark!", and then places the eye within the hollow of the tube...
    ECHO PLAYER The last figure then approaches the bag and pulls a live hawk from it...raising the hawk towards the moon he savagely tears one of the creatures talons from its body and then approaches the bow wielder...intoning, "Mother of nature, the talon of the hawk shall infuse this bow, so that its victims it will always pierce!" and then places the talon into the hollow end of the glass tube.
    ECHO PLAYER The figures then slowly form a circle around the blazing fire and raise their heads to the sky, chanting, "Wise one heed our call, give us your gift to seal our crafting!". The chant continues for a few minutes before you hear the rustling of wings and the distinctive hoot of an owl...scanning the sky for the creature you only see a single feather lazily drifting towards the fire...
    ECHO PLAYER The feather catches a small gust of wind and then floats into the hollow end of the glass bow...as the feather passes the opening the tube quickly seals itself....
    ECHO PLAYER The scene quickly shifts and images flash across your mind...images of the bow being used in battle by mighty chieftains...until a final image etches itself into your mind...you see a proud warrior, his face covered with the proud scars of battle, holding the bow firmly as he gazes up at a sky filled with streaking balls of fire that are descending towards him...
    ECHO PLAYER As this final image fades into oblivion you can hear the proud warrior intone, "We have fought our last battle Tianeki, the fire from the heavens is a foe that can not be defeated..."
    ECHO OTHERS %N seems to be far, far away...
  ENDIF
  IFVERB WIELD -1
    ECHO PLAYER You feel a rush of power flow from the bow to you and images of hunters in flight quickly pass through your mind.
    ECHO OTHERS The bow throbs slightly as %N wields it.
  ENDIF
  IFVERB LOAD -1
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER You sense that the bow does not accept normal arrows.
  ENDIF
  IFVERB RUB -1
    IFITEM -1 WIELDED
      IFVAR ITEMVAL3 ! 1
        ECHO PLAYER The bow vibrates and then you see the material within it flow together and then outwards to form a magnificent arrow.
        EQUAL ITEMVAL3 1
        RANDOM dummy1 1 5 0
        IFVAR dummy1 = 1
          EQUAL ITEMVAL2 27
        ENDIF
        IFVAR dummy1 = 2
          EQUAL ITEMVAL2 29
        ENDIF
        IFVAR dummy1 = 3
          EQUAL ITEMVAL2 31
        ENDIF
        IFVAR dummy1 = 4
          EQUAL ITEMVAL2 33
        ENDIF
        IFVAR dummy1 = 5
          EQUAL ITEMVAL2 35
        ENDIF
        EQUAL ROUNDTIME 3
      ENDIF
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF
;
; I# 9 : Club
INUMBER 9
NAME 53
CRUSH_WEAPON
WEIGHT 8
VOLUME 3
PARAMETER1 9
SUBSTANCE WOOD
CRAFTABLE
ENCRUSTABLE
IFVAR ITEMVAL1 > 600
  IFPREVERB PULL -1
    CLEARVERB
    SUB ITEMVAL1 1
    ECHO PLAYER You concentrate on the club.
    ECHO OTHERS %N concentrates on %a.
    EQUAL RITUALVAL2 111
    SPELL 2 30
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVAR ITEMADJ2 = 644
  IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 600
    IFPREVERB CONC -1
      CLEARVERB
      DAMAGEPLR BODYONLY 300 The club drains part of your life force to recharge itself.
      ADD ITEMVAL1 1
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF
;
; I# 10 : Crossbow (light)
INUMBER 10
NAME 62
BOW_WEAPON
WEIGHT 7
VOLUME 3
PARAMETER1 11
PARAMETER2 4
ENCRUSTABLE
SUBSTANCE WOOD
;
; I# 11 : Crossbow (heavy)
INUMBER 11
NAME 62
BOW_WEAPON
WEIGHT 14
VOLUME 5
PARAMETER1 15
PARAMETER2 4
CRAFTABLE
ENCRUSTABLE
SUBSTANCE WOOD
CONTAINER ON
INTERIOR 1
IFPREVERB LOOK -1
  IFVAR INTNUM3 = 1
    ECHO PLAYER ----%cItembit6 = 1 makes this a double crossbow (ex-593)
    ECHO PLAYER Itembit7 = 1 makes this a 20-rnd stock double crossbow%c----
  ENDIF
  IFVAR ITEMBIT6 = 1
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER This compact crossbow has two bow-strings and two slots for crossbow bolts side by side.
    IFVAR ITEMVAL3 = 0
      ECHO PLAYER It is currently unloaded.
    ENDIF
    IFVAR ITEMVAL3 = 1
      ECHO PLAYER The double crossbow currently has one bolt loaded into it.
    ENDIF
    IFVAR ITEMVAL3 = 2
      ECHO PLAYER It is fully loaded.
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
  IFVAR ITEMBIT7 = 1
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER This compact crossbow has two bow-strings and two slots for crossbow bolts side by side. The mechanism is designed to hold twenty bolts.
    STRCVT 0 ITEMVAL3
    STRCVT 1 ITEMVAL5
    ECHO PLAYER The crossbow has %0 loaded to fire and %1 in the stock.
    ECHO PLAYER %c[LATCH BOLTS to prepare to load a set, then LATCH CROSSBOW to load them]
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVAR ITEMBIT6 = 1
  IFPREVERB LOAD -1
    IFVAR ITEMVAL3 = 1
      EQUAL ITEMBIT0 1
      EQUAL ITEMVAL3 0
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
  IFVERB LOAD -1
    IFVAR ITEMBIT0 = 1
      EQUAL ITEMBIT0 0
      EQUAL ITEMVAL3 2
      ECHO PLAYER You stick a second bolt into the double crossbow.
     ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVAR ITEMBIT7 = 1
  IFPREVERB LATCH -1
    IFVAR FLAG4 ! 0
      CLEARVERB
      ADD ITEMVAL5 FLAG4
      EQUAL FLAG4 0
      IFVAR ITEMVAL5 > 20
        EQUAL ITEMVAL5 20
        ECHO PLAYER You discard the extra bolts in the stock before continuing.
      ENDIF
      EQUAL ROUNDTIME 5
      ECHO PLAYER You load a series of bolts into the stock of your crossbow.%c[Round: 5 sec]
      ECHO OTHERS %N loads a series of bolts into the stock of %a.
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
  IFPREVERB PULL -1
    CLEARVERB
    IFVAR ITEMVAL3 ! 0
      ECHO PLAYER You cannot pull the strings back while there are still bolts loaded.
    ENDIF
    IFVAR ITEMVAL3 = 0
      IFVAR ITEMVAL5 = 0
        ECHO PLAYER The crossbow is empty, you need to load it again before using it.
      ENDIF
      IFVAR ITEMVAL5 ! 0
        SUB ITEMVAL5 2
        EQUAL ITEMVAL3 2
        ECHO PLAYER You pull back the dual strings and two bolts click up and into place from inside the stock.
        ECHO OTHERS %N pulls back the dual strings of %a and two bolts click up into place from inside the stock.
        IFVAR ITEMVAL5 < 1
          ECHO PLAYER The stock clicks as the the mechanism loads the last two bolts.
          ECHO OTHERS You hear %a in %N's hands click as the strings lock into place.
          EQUAL ITEMVAL5 0
        ENDIF      
        EQUAL ROUNDTIME 1
        ECHO PLAYER [Round: 1 sec]
      ENDIF
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF
;
; I# 12 : Dagger
INUMBER 12
NAME 66
PUNCTURE_WEAPON
WEIGHT 2
VOLUME 1
PARAMETER1 3
SUBSTANCE HARDMETAL
CRAFTABLE
ENCRUSTABLE
IFPREVERB LOOK -1
  IFVAR INTNUM3 = 1
    ECHO PLAYER ----%cItembit6 = 1 makes this an attuning dagger. Break a diamond(107) and it gains power in any room whose RNUM/100 = room where diamond broken
    ECHO PLAYER Itembit7 = 1 makes this Moonpie's dagger, casts 318 w/20 sec RT unlimited, uses ITEMVAL1%c----
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB PLAY -1
  IFITEM -1 WIELDED
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER You clean under your fingernails with the dagger.
    ECHO OTHERS %N cleans under %h fingernails with %a.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
ifpreverb latch -1
  clearverb
  ifvar itemadj3 = 272
    echo player You stomp the rusty dagger into dust!
    echo others %N stomps a rusty dagger into dust!
    removeitem -1
  endif
endif
IFVAR ITEMBIT6 = 1
  IFPREVERB WIELD -1
    EQUAL dummy1 RNUM
    MOD dummy1 100
    IFVAR dummy1 = ITEMVAL1
      ECHO PLAYER You feel %a come to life in your hands!
      EQUAL ITEMVAL2 40
      EQUAL ITEMVAL3 2
      EQUAL ITEMVAL5 50
    ELSE
      EQUAL ITEMVAL2 20
      EQUAL ITEMVAL3 10
      EQUAL ITEMVAL5 20
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
  IFPREVERB RECALL -1
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER You recall hearing tales of this weapon. It can attune itself to a particular hunting area. All that is required is to use it to break a large diamond in the area you wish to attune it to, and be willing to sacrifice some of your vitality.
  ENDIF
  IFPREVERB2 BREAK -1
    IFVAR ARCHNUM = 107
      ECHO PLAYER You break %a completely with your dagger.
      ECHO OTHERS %N completely smashes %a into small pieces with %a dagger.
      ECHO ALL The energy from the diamond seems to flow into the weapon!
      REMOVEITEM -1
      SUB QUI 4
      EQUAL ITEMVAL1 RNUM
      MOD ITEMVAL1 100
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVAR ITEMBIT7 = 1
  IFITEM -1 WIELDED
    IFVERB CONCENTRATE -1
      EQUAL ROUNDTIME 20
      SPELL 318
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
  IFPREVERB WIELD -1
    RANDOM dummy1 1 100 0
    EQUAL ITEMVAL1 dummy1
    ADD ITEMVAL1 WIL
    IFVAR ITEMVAL1 < 130
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER The dagger strikes back at you!
      DAMAGEPLR BURN 50 The dagger flares with a burning black fire!
      ECHO OTHERS The dagger seems to suck in the light as it strikes back at %N!
    ENDIF
    IFVAR ITEMVAL1 > 149
      IFVAR ITEMVAL1 < 160
        CLEARVERB
        ECHO PLAYER Something stirs within the dagger and strikes at you!
        DAMAGEPLR BURN 30 The dagger flares with a stinging black flame!
        ECHO OTHERS The dagger almost takes on a life of its own as it struggles with %N.
      ENDIF
    ENDIF
    IFVAR ITEMVAL1 > 159
      ECHO PLAYER The dagger shivers as you gain control of it.
      ECHO OTHERS The dagger shudders as %N wields it.
    ENDIF
    EQUAL ITEMVAL1 0
  ENDIF
ENDIF
