IFPREVERB LOOK -1
  IFVAR INTNUM3 = 1
    ECHO PLAYER ----%cItembit6 = 1 makes this a fiery/icy naginata (ex-553), turn to switch, only changes ITEMVAL3
    ECHO PLAYER Itembit7 = 1 makes this a evil/good slayer naginata (ex-1847), made for Prophet Hunter, push/pull to switch, only changes ITEMVAL3%c----
  ENDIF
  IFVAR ITEMBIT7 = 1
    ECHO PLAYER You see an exceptionally made naginata marked with the sigil of the master
    ECHO PLAYER smith Gruf Steelbender. The weapon has two blades, one made from pure
    ECHO PLAYER albescent, the other from black shadowsteel. A polished randar hilt divides
    ECHO PLAYER the two blades and both of them are coated with tiny diamond chips, adding
    ECHO PLAYER their power to the cutting edge of the blade.
    IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 1
      ECHO PLAYER The pure albescent blade is currently extended for use.
    ENDIF
    IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 2
      ECHO PLAYER The tainted shadowsteel blade is currently extended for use.
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVAR ITEMBIT6 = 1
  IFPREVERB TURN -1
    CLEARVERB
    IFVAR ITEMVAL3 = 2
      EQUAL ITEMVAL3 3
      EQUAL ITEMADJ1 166
      ECHO PLAYER You turn the end of the shaft of %a, causing its blade to freeze.
      ECHO OTHERS %N turns the end of the shaft of %a, causing ice crystals to form on the blade.
    ELSE
      EQUAL ITEMVAL3 2
      EQUAL ITEMADJ1 125
      ECHO PLAYER You turn the end of the shaft of %a, causing flames to appear around its blade.
      ECHO OTHERS %N turns the end of the shaft of %a, causing flames to appear around its blade momentarily.
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
