VOLUME 6
PARAMETER1 18
SUBSTANCE HARDMETAL
CRAFTABLE
ENCRUSTABLE
IFPREVERB LOOK -1
  IFVAR INTNUM3 = 1
    ECHO PLAYER ----%cItembit6 = 1 makes this a special Rorinite longsword (ex-756), 25 charges/game day%c----
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVAR ITEMBIT6 = 1
  EQUAL dummy1 ITEMVAL1
  MOD dummy1 100
  IFVAR dummy1 ! DATE
    EQUAL ITEMVAL1 DATE
    EQUAL ITEMBIT0 0
    EQUAL ITEMBIT1 0
  ENDIF
  IFVERB CONCENTRATE -1
    ECHO PLAYER An image spins before you of Rorin's faithful gathered in the forge of the temple...
    ECHO PLAYER You see Durnik crafting the weapon you now hold in your hand, his body surrounded by Rorin's glow. The other temple members are granting their strength to the ritual and you can see Rorin and Elorna close by, their power flowing into the creation process. You see yourself and your friends moving through the realms of Rorin, each step adding to the power of the weapon in your hand.
    ECHO OTHERS %N's eyes look glassy for a moment.
  ENDIF
  IFPREVERB RUB -1
    CLEARVERB
    IFVAR ITEMVAL1 < 2500
      ECHO PLAYER Brilliant fire flares from the blade and courses into your body as voice booms, "My strength for my faithful follower!"
      ECHO OTHERS Brilliant fire flares up from the blade and courses through %N's body as a booming voice proclaims, "My strength for my faithful follower!"
      SPELL 209 100
      ADD ITEMVAL1 100
    ELSE
      ECHO PLAYER The sword's power has been used up for the day.
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
  IFPREVERB PUSH -1
    CLEARVERB
    IFVAR ITEMVAL1 < 2500
      ECHO PLAYER Silvery threads of power explode from the blade and wrap themselves around you protectively as a silken voice says, "Let no harm come to you, %N."
      ECHO OTHERS Silvery threads of power explode from the blade and wrap themselves around %N protectively as a silken voice says, "Let no harm come to you, %N."
      SPELL 133 100
      ADD ITEMVAL1 100
    ELSE
      ECHO PLAYER The sword's power has been used up for the day.
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
  IFPREVERB CARESS -1
    CLEARVERB
    IFVAR ITEMBIT1 ! 1
      IFVAR REGION = 0
        ECHO PLAYER Beams of golden fire and silver light descend from the sky, forming a stairway before you. You step onto the stairway encased in Rorin and Elorna's power and then find yourself at...
        ECHO OTHERS Beams of golden fire and silver light descend from the sky, forming a brilliant before %N. %N steps onto the stairway and disappears along with it...
        DISBAND
        PLREVENT 2
        CONTPLREVENT
        MOVE 2676
        AFFECT 2676
        ECHO OTHERS A dazzling stairway of gold and silver appears before you. After a moment %N steps off of it.
        IFVAR ITEMBIT0 = 1
          EQUAL ITEMBIT1 1
        ELSE
          EQUAL ITEMBIT0 1
        ENDIF
      ENDIF
      IFVAR REGION ! 0
        ECHO PLAYER That won't work here.
      ENDIF
    ELSE
      ECHO PLAYER That power is used up for the day.
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF
;
; I# 1475 : Broadsword
INUMBER 1475
NAME 1041
SLASH_WEAPON
WEIGHT 17
VOLUME 6
PARAMETER1 19
SUBSTANCE HARDMETAL
CRAFTABLE
ENCRUSTABLE
IFPREVERB LOOK -1
  IFVAR INTNUM3 = 1
    ECHO PLAYER ----%cItembit6 = 1 makes this Sarkathos, the Blade of the Shadows (ex-743), rub/push/pull/kiss, 20 charges/game day
    ECHO PLAYER Itembit7 = 1 makes this a special CB/Kentaurus broadsword (ex-988), push (globe, 2 charges), pull (BR2, 1 charge), 30 charges/game day%c----
  ENDIF
  IFVAR ITEMBIT6 = 1
    ECHO PLAYER Shadows twist and flow along the polished metal of the razor-sharp blade. A row of tiny skulls form the crossguard, the end two slightly large than the rest, with eyes of polished red rubies. The hilt is wrapped in carefully preserved, leathery skin flowing down to the black obsidian orb that serves as the weapon's pommel.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR ITEMBIT7 = 1
    ECHO PLAYER The razor sharp blade gleams brightly in the light, illuminating the
    ECHO PLAYER entirety of the beautiful weapon. The silver crossguard flares out on
    ECHO PLAYER either side, forming intricate dragon heads at the end. The black pommel,
    ECHO PLAYER made of alabaster and carved to look like a beautiful woman, tapers
    ECHO PLAYER down, a large white pearl at the end.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVAR ITEMBIT6 = 1
  EQUAL dummy1 ITEMVAL1
  MOD dummy1 100
  IFVAR dummy1 ! DATE
    EQUAL ITEMVAL1 DATE
  ENDIF
  IFVERB CONCENTRATE -1
    ECHO PLAYER Images and voices fill your head, all clamoring for your attention until your mind's eye can see one black-mailed figure step forth. His eyes glow a dull red as his voice rings through your head...
    ECHO PLAYER "Know that I am Sarkathos, the Blade of the Shadows. In my time I was feared and respected by all who knew my name. My deeds are many, and the foes I have slain are countless."
    ECHO PLAYER "Ever I wandered the world of Andor, pledging my sword to those who studied magic in the darkness. The names of the greatest Necromancers can be counted on the list of those who I have served faithfully."
    ECHO PLAYER "When my time came to pass into the Dark One's waiting embrace, I was granted favor by the one named Malthesia. My soul was bound into this metal, along with the souls of many innocents, so that I would always feed."
    ECHO PLAYER "You who now hold me, realize that we are as one, only those who seek to aid the darkness may call me their blade."
    ECHO PLAYER The voices and images fade from your mind.
    ECHO OTHERS You see the image of a tall, black-mailed warrior appear briefly before %N.
  ENDIF
  IFPREVERB RUB -1
    CLEARVERB
    IFVAR ITEMVAL1 < 2000
      ECHO PLAYER Blood wells up along the blade, flowing into your hand and, thus, into your body, you feel yourself invigorated by the power.
      ECHO OTHERS Blood wells up along the blade of the broadsword and flows into %N's hand.
      SPELL 335 50
      ADD ITEMVAL1 100
    ELSE
      ECHO PLAYER A voice speaks gruffly in your mind, "No more this day! I must feed and rest first."
      ECHO OTHERS %N shakes %h head, as if trying to clear it of  something.
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
  IFPREVERB PUSH -1
    CLEARVERB
    IFVAR ITEMVAL1 < 2000
      ECHO PLAYER The ruby eyes on the skull crossguard glow brightly, the blood-hued light flowing across your body and then seeping deeply into you.
      ECHO OTHERS The ruby eyes on the skull crossguard glow brightly, the blood-hued light flowing across %N's body and then into it.
      SPELL 317 50
      ADD ITEMVAL1 100
    ELSE
      ECHO PLAYER A voice speaks gruffly in your mind, "No more this day! I must feed and rest first."
      ECHO OTHERS %N shakes %h head, as if trying to clear it of  something.
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
  IFPREVERB PULL -1
    CLEARVERB
    IFVAR ITEMVAL1 < 2000
      ECHO PLAYER The ruby eyes on the skull crossguard glow brightly, the blood-hued light flowing across your body and then seeping deeply into you.
      ECHO OTHERS The ruby eyes on the skull crossguard glow brightly, the blood-hued light flowing across %N's body and then into it.
      SPELL 337 50
      ADD ITEMVAL1 100
    ELSE
      ECHO PLAYER A voice speaks gruffly in your mind, "No more this day! I must feed and rest first."
      ECHO OTHERS %N shakes %h head, as if trying to clear it of something.
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
  IFPREVERB KISS -1
    CLEARVERB
    IFVAR ITEMVAL1 < 2000
      ECHO PLAYER Shadows rise from the blade and wrap themselves around you. The darkness flows into your body, and you can feel their energy imbuing your muscles.
      ECHO OTHERS Shadows rise from the blade and wrap themselves around %N. %N seems to grow in size as the shadows are consumed by %h body.
      SPELL 209 100
      ADD ITEMVAL1 100
    ELSE
      ECHO PLAYER A voice speaks gruffly in your mind, "No more this day! I must feed and rest first."
      ECHO OTHERS %N shakes %h head, as if trying to clear it of something.
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVAR ITEMBIT7 = 1
  EQUAL dummy1 ITEMVAL1
  MOD dummy1 100
  IFVAR dummy1 ! DATE
    EQUAL ITEMVAL1 DATE
  ENDIF
  IFVERB CONCENTRATE -1
    ECHO OTHERS %N's eyes glaze over for a moment.
    ECHO PLAYER A series of images flow into your mind. You see the last rays of the sun washing over a battlefield. You can smell the smoke and hear the cries of the wounded. A lone figure moves through the battlefield, stooping over to check bodies every once in a while. You see the figure, a young man, bend over and pick up two banners, one bears the symbol of the Crimson Band, the other the symbol of the Kentaurus family.
    PLREVENT 1
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER The young man begins to run towards the edge of the battlefield, you see a dark figure in pursuit. The young man stumbles and falls, his pursuer falling upon him, sword flashing. The young man fights valiantly, managing to break free, but carrying numerous wounds. He enters the Citadel of the Crimson Band and falls to the floor, his lifeblood seeping onto the cold tiles.
    PLREVENT 1
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER As the last breath fades from the young man's lips he rises up and hands the banners to the Highlord of the Crimson Band and the Patriarch of the Kentaurus Family, saying, "Carry these, with them your armies shall be filled with courage and valor, their morale will never flag...". As the young man's eyes close for the final time, the metal tips of the banners are removed and handed to a waiting smith. The scene shifts to a forge where a smith is seen crafting the weapon you now hold in your hands.
    ECHO OTHERS %N's eyes focus on the real world again.
  ENDIF
  IFPREVERB PULL -1
    CLEARVERB
    IFVAR ITEMVAL1 < 2900
      ECHO PLAYER You feel a wave of light wash over you, emanating from the sword...
      ECHO OTHERS You see the shimmering symbol of the Crimson Band hover above %N for a moment as light washes over %i...
      SPELL 105 30
      ADD ITEMVAL1 200
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
  IFPREVERB PUSH -1
    CLEARVERB
    IFVAR ITEMVAL1 < 3000
      ECHO PLAYER Healing warmth rushes through your body.
      ECHO OTHERS You see the shimmering symbol of the Kentaurus family hover above %N for a brief moment.
      SPELL 317 30
      ADD ITEMVAL1 100
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF
